WEBVTT

00:17.880 --> 00:18.915
<b><font color="#808080">BARBARA:</font></b> <i>First of all,</i>

00:19.120 --> 00:22.590
<i>I realize this is probably not how
you thought the story would start,</i>

00:22.760 --> 00:24.910
<i>not with a big shiny moon</i>

00:25.080 --> 00:27.992
<i>or a city that could look
stunning in spite of itself.</i>

00:28.960 --> 00:30.075
<i>Or me.</i>

00:32.040 --> 00:35.112
<i>But I wanted you to know
that before the horror began,</i>

00:35.280 --> 00:37.635
<i>before it all came crashing down,</i>

00:37.800 --> 00:40.917
<i>there was a time when capes
and cowls and fighting crime</i>

00:41.080 --> 00:42.672
<i>really was exciting.</i>

00:55.560 --> 00:57.630
<i>I'd been with Batman
for almost three years.</i>

00:57.800 --> 01:01.475
<i>That night my father signaled
for him, so something was up.</i>

01:03.920 --> 01:06.036
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BEEPING)</font></b>

01:07.320 --> 01:09.834
<i>I tend to stay out
of these discussions.</i>

01:10.000 --> 01:11.991
<i>I mean, why push my luck?</i>

01:14.520 --> 01:16.238
- <b><font color="#808080">BATMAN:</font></b> <b><font color="#D900D9">(ON RADIO)</font></b> <i>You there?</i>
- Yeah.

01:16.680 --> 01:18.193
We've got a robbery.

01:18.560 --> 01:20.790
<b><font color="#D900D9">(POLICE SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)</font></b>

01:27.240 --> 01:28.240
Bloody son of a...

01:28.440 --> 01:31.113
You act like you've never been
in a police chase before.

01:31.320 --> 01:32.833
- Take the next left.
- Here?

01:33.480 --> 01:34.515
Here.

01:35.640 --> 01:37.232
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

01:40.360 --> 01:41.759
We've got to lose the truck.

01:41.920 --> 01:44.036
Let's lose the cops instead, okay?

01:47.560 --> 01:48.560
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font></b>

02:02.240 --> 02:03.559
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

02:06.720 --> 02:08.870
This is going to be
a night to remember.

02:09.039 --> 02:10.039
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font></b>

02:11.280 --> 02:12.429
Fricking A!

02:14.200 --> 02:15.200
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BEEPING)</font></b>

02:15.400 --> 02:16.879
Caution, falling debris.

02:20.520 --> 02:21.520
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MEN COUGHING)</font></b>

02:24.080 --> 02:25.080
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BEEPS)</font></b>

02:29.920 --> 02:31.069
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

02:33.440 --> 02:35.078
Okay, we lose the truck.

02:36.600 --> 02:37.874
<b><font color="#D900D9">(HISSING)</font></b>

02:47.600 --> 02:48.600
<b><font color="#D900D9">(THUDS)</font></b>

02:48.840 --> 02:49.840
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

02:50.320 --> 02:51.320
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNFIRE)</font></b>

02:57.520 --> 02:58.520
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

03:10.160 --> 03:11.195
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

03:14.280 --> 03:16.589
You really want to turn
a robbery into a murder?

03:16.800 --> 03:18.552
You see another way out of this?

03:19.080 --> 03:21.036
<b><font color="#808080">BATGIRL:</font></b> I know
you're in a bad spot.

03:21.880 --> 03:24.348
But there's bad
and then there's worse.

03:24.800 --> 03:25.949
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE REVVING)</font></b>

03:26.320 --> 03:27.320
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

03:28.160 --> 03:29.195
Like that.

03:30.480 --> 03:31.595
Negotiating?

03:31.760 --> 03:32.909
He wasn't going to hurt me.

03:33.080 --> 03:34.274
Did he know that?

03:34.800 --> 03:37.109
Sometimes, you have
to have a little faith.

03:39.520 --> 03:40.794
What happened to the drivers?

03:40.960 --> 03:42.279
They got away.

03:42.440 --> 03:43.634
But the night's still young.

03:44.880 --> 03:45.880
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font></b>

03:46.040 --> 03:48.349
I'm going to need some alone time.

03:49.280 --> 03:51.236
Oh, sure, yeah.

03:51.400 --> 03:52.992
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MAN GROANING)</font></b>

03:53.160 --> 03:55.594
- Maybe I'll see you...
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMING)</font></b>

03:56.240 --> 03:57.275
Later.

04:09.240 --> 04:10.309
It's a lot of photos.

04:10.520 --> 04:13.557
My uncle's big on family,
even the ones he's hit.

04:18.519 --> 04:20.158
His Holiness is expecting us.

04:23.840 --> 04:25.478
Get the hell in here.

04:28.840 --> 04:30.398
It's all over the news.

04:32.720 --> 04:34.676
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(REMOTE CONTROL CLICKING)</font></b>
<i>- Every channel.</i>

04:37.000 --> 04:39.275
What can I tell you? Batgirl's hot.

04:39.680 --> 04:41.671
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font></b>
- Don't get smart.

04:41.960 --> 04:42.960
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

04:43.480 --> 04:45.391
<i>I lost four men yesterday.</i>

04:45.560 --> 04:46.879
Four idiots.

04:47.040 --> 04:49.873
They said they could
knock out the tracker on the armored car.

04:50.040 --> 04:52.349
I don't think they could plug
a computer in their ass.

04:52.840 --> 04:54.159
Do I care?

04:54.320 --> 04:57.198
I'm out 100 grand,
thanks to your frigging fiasco.

04:57.400 --> 04:58.719
And what do I get for it?

04:58.880 --> 05:01.872
The Bat and his bitch
breathing down my neck.

05:02.560 --> 05:07.588
<i>Bottom line, you're going to give me
my money back, nephew, every cent.</i>

05:08.000 --> 05:13.028
Otherwise you're going to become
a very distant relative, very soon.

05:13.200 --> 05:14.200
<i>Capisce?</i>

05:15.760 --> 05:18.274
Okay, unc, whatever you say.

05:23.560 --> 05:24.754
Darker men, huh?

05:24.920 --> 05:26.200
Barbara, why didn't you tell me?

05:26.280 --> 05:27.920
I have a cousin who's a defense attorney.

05:27.960 --> 05:30.076
Ooh, Reese, not that dark.

05:30.840 --> 05:32.637
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SING-SONG)</font></b> He's single.

05:32.800 --> 05:34.560
Well, that lightens him up
a bit, doesn't it?

05:34.720 --> 05:35.914
Babs, girl,

05:36.080 --> 05:38.416
<b><font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font></b> I do not understand
why you're having fishing troubles

05:38.440 --> 05:40.237
when we are in the middle of a lake.

05:41.240 --> 05:43.356
<i>What do these guys have
to do to get your attention?</i>

05:44.200 --> 05:45.315
Steal a book?

05:45.680 --> 05:47.989
It just so happens
I'm involved with someone.

05:48.200 --> 05:50.270
Sort of, kind of.

05:50.640 --> 05:52.280
- That serious, huh?
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(KEYBOARD CLACKING)</font></b>

05:52.440 --> 05:53.440
What are you doing?

05:53.600 --> 05:55.989
My dad's department
has been setting up city cams.

05:56.160 --> 05:57.593
I've been helping with the program.

05:57.760 --> 06:00.752
It's amazing. You can view
half of Gotham from your computer.

06:00.960 --> 06:02.313
<b><font color="#D900D9">(KEYBOARD CLACKING)</font></b>

06:08.760 --> 06:10.113
<b><font color="#D900D9">(COMPUTER TRILLING)</font></b>

06:13.040 --> 06:15.793
Looks like a bad boy, just your type.

06:27.840 --> 06:29.956
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BEEPING)</font></b>

06:42.320 --> 06:45.915
LONNY: Jesus, Paris, a friggin' fortune
in the middle of some dump.

06:46.080 --> 06:47.115
It's ridiculous.

06:47.280 --> 06:48.998
It used to be a bank.

06:49.160 --> 06:51.958
The same family's owned
this building since 1929.

06:52.120 --> 06:54.031
- Which family?
- My uncle's.

06:54.720 --> 06:56.233
You are bloody crazy.

06:56.400 --> 06:57.435
You sound pissed.

06:57.640 --> 07:00.313
- No, I sound freaked the "F" out.
- I'm not.

07:01.160 --> 07:02.878
And that's freaking me, too.

07:04.280 --> 07:06.316
My uncle's a dinosaur, Lonny.

07:06.480 --> 07:09.552
By the time he finds out
what we've done, he'll be extinct.

07:09.840 --> 07:10.989
<b><font color="#D900D9">(WHIZZING)</font></b>

07:12.720 --> 07:14.517
<b><font color="#808080">BATGIRL:</font></b> No withdrawals
today, boys.

07:14.680 --> 07:15.999
Bloody hell, it's her!

07:17.040 --> 07:19.873
Batgirl, I am impressed.

07:20.080 --> 07:21.911
Where's your overbearing boyfriend?

07:22.080 --> 07:23.354
He's not my boyfriend.

07:24.680 --> 07:26.352
Then maybe I have a chance.

07:26.520 --> 07:27.919
What are you doing?

07:28.080 --> 07:29.559
- I want to meet her.
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(LOUD THUD)</font></b>

07:37.440 --> 07:38.440
<b><font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font></b>

07:40.760 --> 07:42.193
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOT)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

07:43.600 --> 07:45.238
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SLOW CLAPPING)</font></b>

07:46.560 --> 07:47.709
Awesome.

07:49.760 --> 07:50.760
<b><font color="#D900D9">(NECK CRACKS)</font></b>

07:50.920 --> 07:52.240
I don't want to have to hurt you.

07:52.400 --> 07:54.960
Why should you be different
from all the other girls?

07:55.720 --> 07:57.073
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

07:57.320 --> 07:58.548
<b><font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font></b>

07:58.720 --> 08:00.312
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GRUNTING)</font></b>

08:01.640 --> 08:02.709
It's like a dance.

08:02.880 --> 08:04.074
Yeah, right.

08:05.400 --> 08:06.628
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

08:07.640 --> 08:09.596
Too bad we can't sit this one out.

08:09.800 --> 08:11.916
I don't waste my time with punk amateurs.

08:12.080 --> 08:14.674
Oh, baby, I think you've misjudged me.

08:16.280 --> 08:17.280
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

08:22.720 --> 08:24.400
<b><font color="#D900D9">(VOICE ECHOING)</font></b>
Smells like cherries, huh?

08:25.480 --> 08:28.677
You've got maybe
10 seconds to bedtime, baby.

08:28.840 --> 08:30.831
Can't end the night without a kiss.

08:31.920 --> 08:33.433
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

08:34.640 --> 08:36.710
You'll never make it to the door, Batgirl.

08:39.760 --> 08:41.557
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font></b> Smart girl.

08:41.760 --> 08:42.909
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

08:43.120 --> 08:45.395
She's taking a nap. Let's grab the money.

08:46.880 --> 08:48.552
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIREN BLARES)</font></b>

08:49.640 --> 08:51.073
<b><font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)</font></b>

09:08.480 --> 09:09.674
Thanks.

09:10.560 --> 09:11.788
How long was I out?

09:12.520 --> 09:13.555
A few minutes.

09:13.720 --> 09:15.915
Apparently, I got there
right after they left.

09:17.480 --> 09:19.152
You should've waited for me.

09:19.320 --> 09:20.469
They were on their way out.

09:20.640 --> 09:22.198
I had to do something.

09:23.800 --> 09:26.109
His name is Paris, Paris Franz.

09:26.280 --> 09:27.793
<b><font color="#D900D9">(COUGHS)</font></b> You're kidding?

09:30.040 --> 09:31.155
I guess not.

09:32.160 --> 09:33.673
Your father gave me his file.

09:33.880 --> 09:37.190
He's a nasty combination
of narcissist and sociopath.

09:37.360 --> 09:40.079
He'll have you smiling right up to
the moment he cuts your throat.

09:40.480 --> 09:43.517
I haven't had to deal
with his type of crazy in a while.

09:44.400 --> 09:45.833
I don't want you to, either.

09:46.240 --> 09:47.753
What are you saying?

09:47.920 --> 09:49.672
Don't go near him without me.

09:49.840 --> 09:51.876
- Excuse me?
- No matter what.

09:52.040 --> 09:53.837
We're not exactly attached at the hip.

09:54.000 --> 09:55.069
We are on this.

09:55.280 --> 09:57.714
You want to work with me,
you do what I say.

09:58.040 --> 10:00.793
And that's it?
You speak and the words are law?

10:01.200 --> 10:02.269
Yes.

10:06.880 --> 10:07.880
<b><font color="#808080">REESE:</font></b> <i>Let me understand.</i>

10:08.040 --> 10:10.270
<i>You're seeing a guy,
but not really dating.</i>

10:10.440 --> 10:12.351
- Right.
- In a yoga class.

10:12.520 --> 10:13.635
Basically.

10:13.840 --> 10:15.398
He's, like, the instructor?

10:15.560 --> 10:16.595
Right.

10:16.800 --> 10:18.233
And he's making demands?

10:18.400 --> 10:21.198
He's always been controlling,
usually I'm okay with it.

10:21.360 --> 10:22.360
But there's no sex?

10:22.520 --> 10:23.714
God, no!

10:23.880 --> 10:25.791
<i>And you're into him because...</i>

10:27.640 --> 10:29.039
Because of the yoga.

10:29.600 --> 10:30.715
I like the yoga.

10:31.040 --> 10:32.678
So, find another class.

10:33.160 --> 10:35.913
There is no other class, Reese.
This is it.

10:36.080 --> 10:37.080
And I'm good.

10:37.280 --> 10:40.238
He won't say it,
but I'm the best damn student he ever had.

10:40.400 --> 10:42.868
So, if he's going to start
making decisions based on emotions

10:43.040 --> 10:44.519
of which he has zero,

10:44.680 --> 10:46.716
then I think we've got a problem!

10:48.280 --> 10:51.750
And they say the gay scene
is complicated. <b><font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font></b> What?

10:56.960 --> 10:58.393
Here you go, ladies,

10:58.560 --> 11:00.915
added token of our appreciation.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.195
Here's the mask
your buddy wanted me to wear.

11:05.360 --> 11:07.635
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b> Sorry,
we had to cut up the pillowcase.

11:09.080 --> 11:10.433
Got it, thank you.

11:10.600 --> 11:13.239
You know I've got real masks
back at the house,

11:13.440 --> 11:14.509
just saying.

11:26.280 --> 11:27.759
<b><font color="#D900D9">(KEYBOARD CLACKING)</font></b>

11:28.800 --> 11:30.313
So, how long are we going to be here?

11:30.760 --> 11:32.478
I thought you Brits liked the salt air.

11:32.640 --> 11:35.757
I don't like all that money
sitting under a friggin' sink.

11:36.280 --> 11:38.271
- Feed it to the fish.
- What?

11:38.440 --> 11:41.796
I just got access
to every offshore account my uncle owns.

11:42.520 --> 11:43.794
And she called me an amateur.

11:43.960 --> 11:44.995
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CELL PHONE RINGING)</font></b>

11:50.800 --> 11:51.800
<b><font color="#808080">PARIS:</font></b> Who is it?

11:51.960 --> 11:52.960
It's your uncle.

11:53.120 --> 11:54.120
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOT)</font></b>

11:56.080 --> 11:57.593
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNFIRE)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

12:03.480 --> 12:05.357
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNFIRE CONTINUES)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

12:05.520 --> 12:06.635
How do we get out?

12:06.800 --> 12:08.518
You're looking at it.

12:16.680 --> 12:18.796
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BEEPING)</font></b>

12:28.320 --> 12:29.673
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MOTOR REVVING)</font></b>

12:47.840 --> 12:51.150
<i>Batgirl, I'm afraid
I didn't get your number.</i>

12:51.320 --> 12:54.710
<i>So I'm sending this video
to the police to give to you.</i>

12:55.160 --> 12:56.798
<i>They've got to be good for something.</i>

12:57.000 --> 12:59.673
<i>You may have heard
that I've come into some family money.</i>

12:59.880 --> 13:01.279
<i>I told you I'm no punk.</i>

13:01.680 --> 13:04.035
<i>In fact, I got you a gift.</i>

13:04.520 --> 13:07.751
<i>Something special for my special girl.</i>

13:08.480 --> 13:11.392
<i>Just go back to where we met. You'll see.</i>

13:13.360 --> 13:16.113
- Cute.
- It's not cute. It's a trick.

13:16.280 --> 13:18.396
I know, but it is a little flattering.

13:18.560 --> 13:20.198
No, he doesn't know you.

13:20.400 --> 13:21.879
He's objectified you.

13:22.320 --> 13:25.278
When a criminal gets personal like that,
it's bad news.

13:26.240 --> 13:27.389
You're off this one.

13:27.840 --> 13:30.229
- What?
- I don't want you on this case.

13:30.680 --> 13:34.229
At all? So he likes me, we can use that.

13:34.400 --> 13:35.719
He's not afraid of you.

13:35.880 --> 13:37.438
I want him nervous.

13:39.760 --> 13:41.716
The place you met was
at that warehouse, right?

13:41.920 --> 13:43.592
Yeah. Where are you going?

13:43.800 --> 13:46.439
Your father and his men
are already canvassing the place.

13:46.600 --> 13:47.919
I'll let you know what we find.

13:48.080 --> 13:49.911
Hold on, we're not done.

13:50.080 --> 13:52.435
- No, wait. Wait!
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE REVVING)</font></b>

14:10.080 --> 14:11.399
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

14:19.480 --> 14:20.595
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

14:22.200 --> 14:23.428
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE REVVING)</font></b>

14:58.800 --> 14:59.800
<i>Hey!</i>

15:00.800 --> 15:01.994
Is this the gift?

15:02.160 --> 15:03.991
'Cause I thought I was
a little more special.

15:04.480 --> 15:05.629
<i>You are, baby.</i>

15:05.840 --> 15:08.115
<i>But the real gift's somewhere else.</i>

15:08.320 --> 15:10.550
<i>Girls like scavenger hunts, don't they?</i>

15:11.040 --> 15:12.632
Is this going to take long?

15:17.000 --> 15:18.399
<b><font color="#808080">PARIS:</font></b> <i>Careful getting in.</i>

15:18.600 --> 15:20.238
<i>I don't own this place yet.</i>

15:30.920 --> 15:33.798
<i>You're getting hot, hotter.</i>

15:34.560 --> 15:37.154
<i>Whoa, you might have to call
the fire department.</i>

15:49.200 --> 15:52.431
- Where's the gift?
<i>- Come on, look around.</i>

15:52.720 --> 15:54.199
<i>You're the girl detective.</i>

16:03.560 --> 16:04.913
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BATGIRL GRUNTS)</font></b>

16:09.000 --> 16:10.592
<i>For you, my love.</i>

16:10.880 --> 16:12.313
Do you realize what you've done?

16:12.480 --> 16:14.391
He was the biggest boss in Gotham.

16:14.920 --> 16:16.558
He was an artifact.

16:16.720 --> 16:19.359
He went out with phone booths
and the porkpie hat.

16:19.560 --> 16:21.516
I'm the next evolution, baby.

16:21.800 --> 16:25.395
Today, it's all about brains
and nerve and tech.

16:25.560 --> 16:27.152
That's how I got his money

16:27.320 --> 16:28.760
<i>and that's how I'm going to get you.</i>

16:28.920 --> 16:31.000
- <b><font color="#808080">MAN:</font></b> <i>Boss, you okay in there?</i>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(DOORKNOB RATTLING)</font></b>

16:31.160 --> 16:33.280
- You might have to get in line.
- <b><font color="#808080">MAN:</font></b> <i>Break it down.</i>

16:38.000 --> 16:39.319
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

16:40.840 --> 16:41.840
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

16:48.760 --> 16:50.193
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

16:50.600 --> 16:51.669
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

16:52.480 --> 16:53.913
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

16:57.120 --> 16:58.120
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

17:04.800 --> 17:06.472
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)</font></b>

17:15.960 --> 17:18.269
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MEN GROANING)</font></b>

17:35.920 --> 17:37.080
<b><font color="#808080">BATMAN:</font></b> You let him play you.

17:37.240 --> 17:40.516
He thinks he knows you, like there's
some kind of relationship going.

17:40.680 --> 17:42.511
He led you like a lap dog.

17:42.720 --> 17:44.551
Bull, I knew what I was doing.

17:44.720 --> 17:46.597
I was on the hunt, same as you.

17:46.760 --> 17:48.876
No, you were trying to prove something.

17:49.040 --> 17:52.032
You let your ego cloud your judgment.
You should've listened to me.

17:52.200 --> 17:54.634
- I thought we were partners.
- We are.

17:54.920 --> 17:57.753
But we're not equals, not even close.

17:58.000 --> 18:00.150
You sanctimonious, self-righteous...

18:00.320 --> 18:02.390
You're not in it like I am, Barbara.

18:02.680 --> 18:05.240
It's still a game for you,
it's still a thrill.

18:05.400 --> 18:06.992
You haven't been taken to the edge yet.

18:07.320 --> 18:08.548
The edge of what?

18:08.800 --> 18:10.153
The abyss,

18:10.320 --> 18:12.356
the place where you don't care anymore.

18:12.520 --> 18:14.078
Where all hope dies.

18:18.760 --> 18:20.990
We're done here. You're off the case.

18:21.200 --> 18:22.713
No! This isn't over.

18:22.880 --> 18:25.440
You can't dismiss me
with some metaphysical BS.

18:25.600 --> 18:26.999
Why are you doing this?

18:27.160 --> 18:28.832
- I told you.
- Uh-uh.

18:29.040 --> 18:32.032
We've been up against worse threats
than Paris Franz.

18:32.440 --> 18:34.317
This isn't about me, it's about us.

18:34.520 --> 18:37.432
It's about you getting protective
and sitting in judgment.

18:37.800 --> 18:39.199
I won't have it!

18:39.760 --> 18:40.909
Then get out.

18:44.320 --> 18:45.435
How dare you!

18:45.840 --> 18:48.718
I'm in this because of you!
I did what you wanted.

18:48.880 --> 18:49.995
I made it work!

18:50.560 --> 18:51.560
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

18:58.560 --> 18:59.560
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BATMAN GROANS)</font></b>

18:59.720 --> 19:02.154
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GRUNTING)</font></b>

19:02.320 --> 19:03.435
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

19:10.520 --> 19:11.520
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BATGIRL MOANS)</font></b>

19:47.440 --> 19:51.274
Barbara Kathleen Gordon,
what the hell have you done?

19:52.920 --> 19:54.956
So, you and yoga guy?

19:55.280 --> 19:57.396
Yeah, a few nights ago.

19:57.600 --> 20:00.114
Girl, you've been holding out. How was it?

20:01.760 --> 20:05.230
- Not so good?
- No, it was fantastic...

20:06.280 --> 20:08.032
Like fireworks.

20:08.200 --> 20:09.200
Yeah?

20:09.360 --> 20:11.555
Except he's been avoiding me.

20:11.720 --> 20:13.631
At least, I think he is.

20:13.800 --> 20:14.869
We haven't talked.

20:15.040 --> 20:16.234
I've been to that dance.

20:16.880 --> 20:19.952
Maybe it was too soon,
even after all this time.

20:20.960 --> 20:23.952
Talk to him, Babs.
Some guys need a period of adjustment.

20:24.160 --> 20:26.310
They get nervous about commitment.

20:26.480 --> 20:27.674
He's only human, right?

20:32.840 --> 20:35.115
<b><font color="#D900D9">(REPORTER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY ON TV)</font></b>

20:36.240 --> 20:38.549
<b><font color="#808080">REPORTER:</font></b> <i>In local news,
the city is bracing for gang wars</i>

20:38.720 --> 20:42.269
<i>following the murder of crime boss,
Carlos Francesco, Saturday.</i>

20:42.440 --> 20:45.671
<i>At the same time, the manhunt
goes on for Parry Francesco,</i>

20:45.840 --> 20:48.400
<i>aka Paris Franz, the murder suspect.</i>

20:48.600 --> 20:50.158
<i>Said Detective Harvey Bullock,</i>

20:50.320 --> 20:52.440
<i>"It's like he's fallen off
the face of the Earth... "</i>

20:52.560 --> 20:53.993
From your lips, Harvey.

20:54.160 --> 20:55.991
<b><font color="#D900D9">(REPORTER CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)</font></b>

20:58.280 --> 21:00.510
But I tried to be what you want.

21:00.680 --> 21:02.080
You're not listening to me, Debbie.

21:02.200 --> 21:05.556
So damn clingy.
I feel trapped, like I can't move.

21:05.880 --> 21:07.279
I need space.

21:07.800 --> 21:08.949
Hey, hey, hey!

21:09.560 --> 21:10.754
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MAN GROANS)</font></b>

21:11.400 --> 21:13.550
There... Space.

21:21.320 --> 21:23.231
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BIRDS COOING)</font></b>

21:33.280 --> 21:35.191
So, what do you think?

21:36.040 --> 21:37.439
Is it worth a shot?

21:40.720 --> 21:41.789
I'm doing it, anyway.

21:49.840 --> 21:51.068
<b><font color="#D900D9">(RADIO BUZZING)</font></b>

21:59.800 --> 22:00.869
Hey.

22:01.080 --> 22:05.710
Hi, nothing on cable tonight, so I thought
I'd get out and get some exercise.

22:06.040 --> 22:08.190
Tell me, how's Paris these days?

22:08.360 --> 22:09.554
<i>He's on the move.</i>

22:09.760 --> 22:12.752
We got a tip
he might be hiding out at the docks.

22:12.920 --> 22:14.239
That's where I am right now.

22:17.120 --> 22:19.031
That wouldn't be an invitation, would it?

22:19.200 --> 22:20.200
<i>No.</i>

22:20.400 --> 22:21.992
I was just kidding,

22:22.160 --> 22:23.479
but I'm not that far away.

22:23.640 --> 22:24.640
No.

22:24.800 --> 22:27.439
<i>But what about after you get him?
What then?</i>

22:29.280 --> 22:30.599
Are we back in business?

22:33.800 --> 22:35.279
Oh, come on!

22:35.440 --> 22:36.668
<i>We'll talk later.</i>

22:37.280 --> 22:38.838
It was just sex for God's sake.

22:39.040 --> 22:40.360
It doesn't have to mean anything.

22:40.440 --> 22:42.160
It's not like we have to care,
I don't care.

22:42.320 --> 22:45.437
You don't care.
We just go back like it was. That's all.

22:45.680 --> 22:46.908
<i>Please.</i>

22:47.960 --> 22:49.029
Later.

23:05.760 --> 23:06.875
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

23:15.640 --> 23:16.675
Bang on, mate!

23:21.680 --> 23:22.795
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BEEPING)</font></b>

23:23.160 --> 23:24.639
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

23:33.400 --> 23:34.674
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

23:40.080 --> 23:41.080
<b><font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES)</font></b>

23:50.520 --> 23:52.192
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING IN PAIN)</font></b>

23:56.760 --> 23:58.113
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

24:15.360 --> 24:16.588
Take the other side.

24:18.400 --> 24:19.400
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

24:29.120 --> 24:30.269
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECH)</font></b>

24:41.880 --> 24:43.074
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

24:43.240 --> 24:44.275
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font></b>

24:47.880 --> 24:49.552
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

24:50.920 --> 24:52.239
Alone at last.

24:54.920 --> 24:56.399
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GRUNTING)</font></b>

25:04.200 --> 25:07.875
Selfish, foul, piece of garbage!

25:08.080 --> 25:09.672
You ruined everything!

25:10.720 --> 25:12.676
Must be that time of the month.

25:13.720 --> 25:14.720
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

25:16.040 --> 25:17.519
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BATGIRL GRUNTING)</font></b>

25:27.600 --> 25:29.318
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

25:29.920 --> 25:31.433
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

25:34.040 --> 25:35.040
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font></b>

25:42.880 --> 25:44.199
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PARIS WHEEZING)</font></b>

25:53.640 --> 25:55.471
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIRENS APPROACHING)</font></b>

26:20.680 --> 26:23.148
<i>Thanks to Batman,
Franz was taken into police custody,</i>

26:23.320 --> 26:25.515
<i>ending an intensive city-wide search.</i>

26:26.320 --> 26:29.551
<i>This was the scene earlier today
as he was taken into arraignment.</i>

26:30.640 --> 26:32.915
<i>Love you, Batgirl. Love you.</i>

26:49.600 --> 26:50.669
Batgirl.

26:53.320 --> 26:54.320
Close.

26:57.120 --> 26:59.714
I thought I'd save you
the trouble of ending this.

27:01.680 --> 27:03.511
There's some stuff you might want back.

27:04.600 --> 27:07.273
Can't have smoke bombs
exploding in the apartment.

27:08.040 --> 27:09.553
I'm sorry, it's just that...

27:09.720 --> 27:12.757
I get it. It's one thing
to protect the city,

27:12.920 --> 27:15.309
another when it
narrows down to one person.

27:16.600 --> 27:18.113
Someone you really care about.

27:20.800 --> 27:22.711
I'll find some way to fill my time.

27:24.400 --> 27:25.958
It's just as well, you know.

27:27.440 --> 27:30.034
I saw that abyss you spoke about,

27:30.200 --> 27:33.192
very scary, but so tempting.

27:34.360 --> 27:36.032
<i>I don't know how you resist it.</i>

27:38.040 --> 27:40.918
I don't think it's humanly possible
after a while.

27:42.760 --> 27:43.954
Be careful.

27:48.160 --> 27:49.673
<b><font color="#808080">BARBARA:</font></b>
<i>And that was that.</i>

27:49.840 --> 27:53.230
<i>Oh, I'd see him again,
but never as Batgirl.</i>

27:53.440 --> 27:55.271
<i>I really was done
with that part of my life.</i>

27:56.120 --> 27:58.588
<i>A week later, it wouldn't matter anyway.</i>

27:58.760 --> 28:00.637
<i>A terrible storm was moving in</i>

28:00.800 --> 28:02.836
<i>and we'd all be in for it by then.</i>

28:17.960 --> 28:19.951
<b><font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)</font></b>

28:53.080 --> 28:54.559
Hell of a night, huh?

28:54.720 --> 28:57.234
What makes it different
from any other night in Gotham?

28:57.760 --> 29:00.718
Nothing, nothing at all, I suppose.

29:01.400 --> 29:04.995
Commissioner Gordon, uh,
he thought you might like to see this.

29:06.440 --> 29:09.352
- That's an interesting choice of words.
- Come again?

29:09.560 --> 29:11.516
Why would I "like" to see this?

29:11.800 --> 29:12.800
Huh.

29:13.160 --> 29:16.311
Well, I guess "need"
would have been better for you, right?

29:16.840 --> 29:18.876
<i>Coroner came and gave things the eyeball.</i>

29:19.240 --> 29:22.357
<i>Says these poor saps died
probably three years ago.</i>

29:23.520 --> 29:24.555
Died?

29:24.720 --> 29:28.679
Well, we won't know for sure if they was
murdered till after the autopsies.

29:28.920 --> 29:30.319
They were murdered.

29:30.920 --> 29:32.433
What do you make of this?

29:32.880 --> 29:34.791
What do I make?
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font></b>

29:35.000 --> 29:38.515
Well, three years ago
was that dentists' convention.

29:38.680 --> 29:41.797
The one where a handful of conventioneers
never returned home,

29:42.120 --> 29:43.155
just went missing.

29:43.320 --> 29:45.880
Emptied out their bank accounts
and disappeared.

29:46.080 --> 29:48.389
I think we're standing
in the mouth of that.

29:48.560 --> 29:51.472
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b> It's an interesting
choice of words, huh?

29:52.960 --> 29:54.916
<b><font color="#808080">BATMAN:</font></b> Tell Gordon
I'd like to talk to him.

29:56.040 --> 29:58.600
Well, I would,
but tonight's his father-daughter night

29:58.760 --> 29:59.829
and you know he doesn't...

30:00.000 --> 30:01.115
Have to be there.

30:01.320 --> 30:03.311
Tell Gordon I need to talk...

30:03.720 --> 30:04.720
To him.

30:11.640 --> 30:13.073
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

30:29.760 --> 30:30.954
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

30:31.280 --> 30:32.793
<b><font color="#D900D9">(EXHALES)</font></b>

30:40.440 --> 30:41.953
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font></b>

30:46.560 --> 30:48.278
- Hello?
- <b><font color="#808080">GORDON:</font></b> <i>Barbara, it's Dad.</i>

30:48.440 --> 30:49.953
Oh, hi, Dad, how's your day?

30:50.160 --> 30:51.639
<i>Not over yet, unfortunately.</i>

30:51.800 --> 30:53.736
<i>I'm sorry, honey,
but I won't be able to make it tonight.</i>

30:53.760 --> 30:55.637
<i>- Something's come up.</i>
- Are you all right?

30:55.800 --> 30:57.836
<i>I'm fine, there's nothing
for you to worry about.</i>

30:58.040 --> 30:59.632
<i>A friend asked me for a favor.</i>

30:59.800 --> 31:00.949
A friend?

31:01.120 --> 31:03.588
<i>Yes, honey, that friend.</i>

31:04.680 --> 31:05.680
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECH)</font></b>

31:22.240 --> 31:24.390
You mind telling me what this is about?

31:32.160 --> 31:33.991
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SCRAPING)</font></b>

31:37.200 --> 31:38.315
<b><font color="#808080">GORDON:</font></b> Listen to me.

31:38.480 --> 31:40.789
He's been in custody for two years.

31:41.000 --> 31:42.797
If we can prove what we found today...

31:43.000 --> 31:45.230
- <b><font color="#808080">BATMAN:</font></b> He'll confess.
- <b><font color="#808080">GORDON:</font></b> He's insane.

31:45.400 --> 31:47.550
It's a mistake to think
you know what he'll do.

31:51.960 --> 31:53.996
I'm not here
because of what was found today.

31:55.280 --> 31:56.554
<b><font color="#D900D9">(KEYS JANGLING)</font></b>

31:58.520 --> 32:00.351
I'm here because I need to be.

32:10.480 --> 32:12.994
Hello, I want to talk.

32:19.200 --> 32:22.556
I've been thinking lately
about you, you and me.

32:23.040 --> 32:24.792
About how this is going to end.

32:25.040 --> 32:27.031
About who will end up killing who.

32:29.520 --> 32:33.035
Perhaps, you'll kill me,
perhaps I'll kill you,

32:33.520 --> 32:38.150
perhaps sooner, perhaps later,
you know that, don't you?

32:41.720 --> 32:44.757
I just, I need to know,

32:44.920 --> 32:46.990
for when that time comes,

32:47.160 --> 32:50.277
that I'd made a genuine attempt
to talk things over,

32:50.440 --> 32:54.319
to try and avert the inevitable,
just once.

32:57.040 --> 32:59.952
Listen to me, this is life and death,

33:00.160 --> 33:01.878
mine or yours.

33:02.120 --> 33:06.113
Our relationship, it's fatal.
I don't want your murder on my...

33:10.640 --> 33:12.949
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font></b> Hey, wait a minute.
I've got rights.

33:13.400 --> 33:14.913
You ain't allowed to touch me!

33:15.920 --> 33:17.353
Where is he?

33:17.520 --> 33:19.112
Do you realize what you've set free?

33:19.280 --> 33:22.750
What it's capable of?
Do you have any idea?

33:23.160 --> 33:24.229
Where is he?

33:24.400 --> 33:27.040
- Dear God, open that door!
- <b><font color="#808080">IMPOSTOR:</font></b> <b><font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERING)</font></b> <i>Get off of me!<</i>

33:27.440 --> 33:28.680
What do you think you're doing?

33:28.840 --> 33:30.592
You know the laws
about mistreating inmates.

33:30.760 --> 33:32.796
If you harm one hair on his head...

33:34.480 --> 33:37.233
Now, you stinking little stain!

33:37.400 --> 33:40.472
I'm going to ask you politely,
one last time.

33:40.640 --> 33:41.834
Where is he?

33:43.280 --> 33:44.838
<b><font color="#808080">CARNY OWNER:</font></b>
<i>Ah, there you are.</i>

33:45.600 --> 33:47.750
<i>So, had enough time
to look over the property?</i>

33:48.120 --> 33:49.678
It's what you're looking for?

33:49.920 --> 33:53.196
Well, it's garish, ugly
and smells like piss.

33:53.360 --> 33:57.148
Can't quite make out
whether it's bums or rats, but it's piss.

33:57.320 --> 34:00.357
I'm a connoisseur
when it comes to eau de toilette.

34:00.520 --> 34:01.999
As for the rides,

34:02.160 --> 34:07.154
any innocent little child
getting on one could be maimed or worse.

34:09.480 --> 34:11.197
So you don't like it?

34:11.639 --> 34:13.277
Don't like it?

34:13.480 --> 34:15.994
I'm crazy for it!
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b>

34:16.159 --> 34:18.196
Okay, okay, that's great.

34:19.360 --> 34:22.716
So the price, with what you've
mentioned, we can negotiate.

34:23.199 --> 34:26.875
No need to, sure your price is steep,
but as I look around,

34:27.080 --> 34:30.072
all I can see is I'll be making a killing.

34:30.719 --> 34:32.915
And money? Not a problem.

34:33.800 --> 34:34.994
Not anymore.

34:37.600 --> 34:39.716
How'd it go? Did they like your act?

34:41.000 --> 34:42.672
Well, they, uh...

34:42.920 --> 34:44.638
They said they might call me.

34:45.679 --> 34:47.716
I got nervous and blew a punch line.

34:49.760 --> 34:50.760
Oh.

34:51.320 --> 34:52.594
What do you mean, "Oh"?

34:52.880 --> 34:54.871
I didn't mean anything.

34:55.040 --> 34:58.999
Yes, you did,
the way you said "oh" like that.

34:59.280 --> 35:00.838
Jesus, all I said was...

35:01.000 --> 35:02.149
You said, "Oh."

35:02.320 --> 35:03.856
As in, "Oh, so you didn't get the job?"

35:03.880 --> 35:05.313
As in, "Oh, I should've known?"

35:05.480 --> 35:07.755
As in, "Oh, so how are we going
to feed our baby?"

35:07.920 --> 35:10.195
You think I'm not worried about that?

35:10.520 --> 35:12.795
You think it's all a big joke to me?

35:13.000 --> 35:15.389
I have to go up on stage

35:15.560 --> 35:17.994
and nobody laughs.

35:18.160 --> 35:19.878
And you think I don't care.

35:20.040 --> 35:22.679
You think, you think...
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CRYING)</font></b>

35:23.800 --> 35:26.872
Oh, God! Oh, God! I'm sorry!

35:27.840 --> 35:29.796
I don't mean to take this out on you.

35:29.960 --> 35:31.598
You're suffering enough,

35:31.760 --> 35:33.637
being married to a loser.

35:34.440 --> 35:37.352
- Honey, that's not...
- Yes, it is true.

35:37.880 --> 35:39.677
I can't support you.

35:40.040 --> 35:41.075
Oh, Jeannie.

35:41.640 --> 35:43.039
Shh. It'll be okay.

35:43.280 --> 35:45.555
The baby won't be here
for another three months.

35:45.720 --> 35:48.280
Mrs. Berkis will let us slide
on the rent a little longer,

35:48.440 --> 35:50.078
she feels sorry for me.

35:50.680 --> 35:52.318
She hates me.

35:52.560 --> 35:56.917
She comes out in the hallway to scowl
at me every time I take the stairs.

35:57.600 --> 36:00.592
That smell like cat litter and old people.

36:01.560 --> 36:05.030
I've just got to get you out of here
before the baby comes.

36:06.880 --> 36:11.032
All I need is enough money
to get us set up in a decent neighborhood.

36:11.200 --> 36:12.235
For crying out loud,

36:12.440 --> 36:15.238
there are girls on the street
who earn that in a weekend

36:15.600 --> 36:18.068
without having to tell a single joke

36:18.280 --> 36:19.838
or blow a punch line.

36:20.000 --> 36:21.592
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font></b>

36:22.240 --> 36:24.435
Come here and stop worrying about us.

36:24.760 --> 36:27.194
I love you, job or no job.

36:27.400 --> 36:29.834
You're good in the sack
and you make me laugh.

36:31.720 --> 36:33.280
<b><font color="#808080">CARNY OWNER:</font></b>
<i>Let me tell you something.</i>

36:33.320 --> 36:35.356
You ain't going to regret
buying this place.

36:35.560 --> 36:37.152
It ain't as bad as it looks.

36:37.600 --> 36:39.431
I hope you're wrong about that.

36:40.040 --> 36:41.917
Come on, a little spit and polish,

36:42.080 --> 36:44.116
you'll have yourself
one hell of a carnival.

36:44.480 --> 36:46.118
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b>
Oh, you are so right,

36:46.280 --> 36:48.953
and thanks to your smooth salesmanship

36:49.120 --> 36:53.113
and your silver tongue,
I'm completely sold.

36:53.280 --> 36:54.633
Let's shake on it.

36:54.880 --> 36:56.871
Sure, sure, it's my privilege.

36:57.040 --> 36:59.600
Yes, yes, it is.

37:01.280 --> 37:02.474
Who are they?

37:02.640 --> 37:05.473
Spit and Polish, my attorneys.

37:05.640 --> 37:08.632
They persuaded your partner
to sign over the deed about an hour ago.

37:08.800 --> 37:10.916
The property's already mine.

37:11.520 --> 37:14.512
I can see that you're happy about that.

37:14.680 --> 37:16.113
Now, I must dash.

37:16.280 --> 37:19.113
There's equipment to rent,
plus workers to hire,

37:19.280 --> 37:22.113
and of course,
I need to secure my main attraction.

37:22.440 --> 37:24.396
Uh, do feel free to stick around.

37:50.400 --> 37:52.709
Your refreshments, Master Bruce.

37:54.560 --> 37:55.595
Well, then, sir,

37:55.760 --> 37:58.797
do you need my further assistance
or should I just go away?

37:59.000 --> 38:00.353
That'll be fine.

38:00.520 --> 38:03.114
Trying to figure out
what he intends to do.

38:03.280 --> 38:05.236
It's almost impossible.

38:05.400 --> 38:08.358
Excuse me if I find that comforting, sir.

38:08.560 --> 38:09.834
I don't know him, Alfred.

38:10.280 --> 38:14.319
<i>All these years and I don't know who he is
any more than he knows who I am.</i>

38:14.600 --> 38:16.238
Are you sure of that?

38:16.640 --> 38:17.640
What do you mean?

38:17.800 --> 38:20.155
I mean don't underestimate him.

38:21.040 --> 38:24.589
I don't and neither should he
underestimate me.

38:26.520 --> 38:28.715
You can't save everyone, sir.

38:33.080 --> 38:34.274
He drives me.

38:34.440 --> 38:37.989
<i>How can two people hate so much
without knowing each other?</i>

38:40.560 --> 38:46.635
I hate this. Whenever we jail him, I pray,
"Please, God, just keep him there."

38:46.920 --> 38:48.273
And then when he escapes, it's,

38:48.440 --> 38:50.908
"Please don't let him
do something too awful this time."

38:51.080 --> 38:52.080
I hate it.

38:52.240 --> 38:55.630
Dad, just once, could you leave
your work at the office and relax?

38:56.120 --> 38:57.599
I made you some cocoa.

38:58.840 --> 39:01.593
Thanks, but tonight
I could use something a little stiffer.

39:03.080 --> 39:05.310
You know, I found that
Catwoman scrapbook you couldn't.

39:05.480 --> 39:07.072
It was behind the wardrobe.

39:08.600 --> 39:11.319
You really ought to let me work
out a filing system for you,

39:11.600 --> 39:13.318
something like we use at the library.

39:14.160 --> 39:15.559
<b><font color="#808080">GORDON:</font></b> Mmm-hmm.

39:16.480 --> 39:17.629
Oh, look.

39:17.800 --> 39:20.394
You've got paste squidging out,
don't get it on your pants.

39:20.560 --> 39:22.949
Barbara, I swear,
you're fussier than your mother was.

39:23.120 --> 39:24.314
<b><font color="#D900D9">(KNOCK AT DOOR)</font></b>

39:24.480 --> 39:26.232
That must be Colleen. She's early.

39:26.400 --> 39:27.549
We're going to work out.

39:27.760 --> 39:29.416
You'll have to entertain her
while I get ready.

39:29.440 --> 39:32.637
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b> Look at this one.
First time they met.

39:32.800 --> 39:35.633
He was just robbing banks then. Remember?

39:35.800 --> 39:38.917
What I remember is you describing
his white face and green hair.

39:39.080 --> 39:41.230
I was just a kid,
scared the hell out of me.

39:41.440 --> 39:42.936
<b><font color="#808080">GORDON:</font></b> I thought
you'd be interested.

39:42.960 --> 39:46.191
Yeah, well, I had some
really interesting nightmares.

39:55.840 --> 39:56.840
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOT)</font></b>

39:58.480 --> 39:59.879
<b><font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font></b>

40:03.400 --> 40:04.400
Barbara!

40:04.600 --> 40:05.999
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

40:07.000 --> 40:09.434
<b><font color="#808080">JOKER:</font></b> <i>I wouldn't worry yet,
if I were you.</i>

40:09.600 --> 40:11.830
It's just a psychological manifestation,

40:12.000 --> 40:13.831
common among librarians.

40:14.000 --> 40:16.355
<i>She thinks she's a coffee table edition,</i>

40:16.520 --> 40:19.432
though I can't say much
for this volume's condition.

40:19.640 --> 40:21.676
I mean there's a hole in the jacket

40:21.840 --> 40:24.798
and the spine appears to be damaged.

40:25.280 --> 40:27.157
You scum, I'll...

40:27.360 --> 40:28.360
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

40:29.640 --> 40:30.640
Will you?

40:30.800 --> 40:33.837
Refreshing to hear, not by the book.

40:34.000 --> 40:38.437
Speaking of which, this one won't be
walking off the shelf anytime soon.

40:38.600 --> 40:42.195
In fact, the idea
of her walking anywhere seems remote.

40:42.360 --> 40:46.148
But then, that's always
a problem with softbacks.

40:46.320 --> 40:47.514
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CLICKS TONGUE)</font></b> Oh, God,

40:47.680 --> 40:50.877
literary discussions
can get so dry, can't they?

40:51.040 --> 40:55.238
Finish the Commissioner, take him where he
needs to be and please, do be careful.

40:55.400 --> 40:58.551
After all, he is topping the bill.

41:00.040 --> 41:04.113
It really is a shame you'll miss
your father's debut, Ms. Gordon.

41:05.200 --> 41:07.714
Sadly, our venue wasn't built

41:07.880 --> 41:09.711
- for the disabled in mind.
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font></b>

41:09.880 --> 41:13.589
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>
Why are you doing this?

41:14.840 --> 41:16.558
To prove a point.

41:17.440 --> 41:18.873
Here's to crime.

41:24.280 --> 41:27.033
You see, I have a reason, a good one.

41:27.400 --> 41:29.152
I have to prove myself...

41:31.720 --> 41:33.790
As a husband and a father.

41:34.400 --> 41:38.359
I mean, well, this isn't the sort of thing
I'd agree to do normally,

41:38.520 --> 41:40.351
without an important reason.

41:40.760 --> 41:41.760
Of course.

41:42.280 --> 41:44.919
Did I ever tell you
I started out as a lab assistant?

41:45.080 --> 41:46.354
Of course, I did, right?

41:46.560 --> 41:49.836
<i>A good job, a real good job,
but my heart wasn't in it.</i>

41:50.440 --> 41:54.228
So, I quit to be a comedian,
to make people laugh

41:54.400 --> 41:56.470
because when they laugh, they feel good.

41:56.640 --> 41:59.029
The thing is... <b><font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font></b>
They didn't.

41:59.240 --> 42:00.468
Now I'm not feeling good.

42:00.640 --> 42:03.029
That's why I'm here, for one big score!

42:03.200 --> 42:05.236
Hey, can you try and be cool?

42:06.720 --> 42:10.269
Sorry, I usually don't drink at lunchtime.

42:10.440 --> 42:12.670
You're not lying when you say
we'll get away with it?

42:12.880 --> 42:14.632
Nobody will know I was involved?

42:14.840 --> 42:17.274
Not to worry, friend.
We'll take care of you.

42:17.440 --> 42:20.201
We need your help getting into that
chemical plant you used to work in

42:20.280 --> 42:22.350
and into the playing card company
next door.

42:22.560 --> 42:24.676
It's your expertise we appreciate.

42:24.840 --> 42:28.628
And to absolutely guarantee
ain't nobody connects you to the robbery,

42:30.480 --> 42:32.072
you'll be wearing this.

42:33.800 --> 42:35.711
Wait a minute,

42:35.880 --> 42:37.791
I've seen that before in the papers.

42:38.680 --> 42:40.796
That's the Red Hood's mask.

42:40.960 --> 42:42.757
He raided that ice company last month.

42:42.920 --> 42:44.638
Smarten up, wise guy.

42:44.800 --> 42:46.358
There ain't no Red Hood.

42:46.520 --> 42:50.035
Just a bunch of guys
like yourself and a mask.

42:50.200 --> 42:52.760
Right, the most valued member of the crew,

42:52.960 --> 42:55.428
he gets to wear it, no questions asked.

42:55.600 --> 42:57.033
'Cause he needs the...

42:57.200 --> 42:59.270
"He can't afford to be
connected to the job

42:59.440 --> 43:02.238
"so he deserves additional anonymity."

43:02.400 --> 43:03.515
Merits it.

43:03.720 --> 43:07.110
Sure. That makes sense, right? That's you.

43:07.280 --> 43:08.838
But there aren't any eye slits.

43:09.000 --> 43:10.319
How am I supposed to see?

43:10.520 --> 43:12.511
Well, therein lies the beauty.

43:12.680 --> 43:15.672
Two-way mirrors,
just like the cops use, huh?

43:15.840 --> 43:19.469
I don't know, I don't know.

43:19.760 --> 43:21.478
That chemical plant...

43:21.640 --> 43:24.518
I quit 'cause it creeped me out.

43:24.680 --> 43:28.832
So grim and ugly,
it was getting under my skin.

43:29.160 --> 43:31.116
But you know it
like the back of your hand.

43:31.280 --> 43:32.395
Right.

43:32.560 --> 43:34.118
But this ain't about you, though.

43:34.680 --> 43:37.513
No. No, of course not.

43:37.840 --> 43:39.273
Just this once,

43:39.440 --> 43:41.112
then I can lead a proper life.

43:41.280 --> 43:42.429
Exactly.

43:42.640 --> 43:45.200
Can't make a nest
without breaking a few eggs.

43:45.960 --> 43:47.871
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b> That's funny.

43:48.200 --> 43:50.191
No, it's cliche.

43:50.720 --> 43:53.473
So, 11:00, Friday night,

43:54.400 --> 43:55.400
friend?

43:56.320 --> 43:59.551
Starting Saturday morning, I'll be rich.

43:59.720 --> 44:02.917
Just trying to imagine that,
my life, completely changed.

44:03.720 --> 44:05.551
Nothing will be the same...

44:07.080 --> 44:08.718
Not ever again.

44:18.160 --> 44:19.388
<b><font color="#D900D9">(POWERING UP)</font></b>

44:29.280 --> 44:30.599
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MONITOR BEEPING)</font></b>

45:01.360 --> 45:03.191
She'll never walk again.

45:03.840 --> 45:04.955
I'm sorry.

45:10.680 --> 45:14.673
Some woman found Ms. Gordon,
name of Colleen Miles.

45:15.120 --> 45:19.671
She found the, uh, victim
in a state of undress.

45:20.240 --> 45:21.468
Undress?

45:22.320 --> 45:23.912
They didn't tell you?

45:24.080 --> 45:25.399
Pretty sick, ain't it?

45:27.840 --> 45:29.478
Leave us alone for a moment.

45:42.960 --> 45:46.111
Barbara, I don't know if you can hear me.

45:47.240 --> 45:48.240
<b><font color="#808080">BARBARA:</font></b> Batman?

45:49.840 --> 45:50.989
Batman.

45:58.240 --> 46:00.231
He took Dad, he...

46:00.960 --> 46:03.599
Oh, God! I remember.

46:03.880 --> 46:06.235
Barbara, take it easy. It's okay.

46:06.400 --> 46:07.992
No, no, it's not okay.

46:08.400 --> 46:10.436
<i>He's taking it to the limit this time.</i>

46:10.680 --> 46:12.875
You didn't see his eyes.

46:13.080 --> 46:15.833
He said he wanted to prove a point.

46:16.040 --> 46:18.156
Said Dad was top of the bill.

46:18.320 --> 46:21.118
What's he going to do?
What's he going to do to my father?

46:22.560 --> 46:24.551
Huh? What?

46:25.280 --> 46:26.599
- Wait!
- Up!

46:27.560 --> 46:29.630
Stop! <b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font></b>

46:29.800 --> 46:30.800
Up!

46:31.160 --> 46:33.037
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

46:36.520 --> 46:37.953
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font></b>

46:42.040 --> 46:43.040
<b><font color="#808080">GORDON:</font></b> <i>No, no!</i>

46:43.400 --> 46:44.833
Don't, please.

46:45.000 --> 46:46.558
Why are you doing this?

46:47.400 --> 46:49.038
Where are you taking me?

46:49.360 --> 46:50.360
- Down!
- What?

46:50.520 --> 46:51.999
- Down!
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

46:52.880 --> 46:55.997
Please, tell me what I'm doing here.

46:56.160 --> 46:57.639
Somebody!

46:57.800 --> 46:58.915
<b><font color="#808080">JOKER:</font></b> <i>Doing?</i>

46:59.080 --> 47:02.914
You're doing what any sane man in your
appalling circumstances would do.

47:03.640 --> 47:05.073
You're going mad.

47:06.280 --> 47:08.350
I remember.

47:08.520 --> 47:10.715
<b><font color="#808080">JOKER:</font></b> <b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS MANIACALLY)</font></b>
<i>I wouldn't do that.</i>

47:10.880 --> 47:13.269
Remembering's dangerous.

47:13.440 --> 47:16.989
I find the past such
a worrying, anxious place.

47:17.320 --> 47:20.756
Yes, memory is so treacherous.

47:20.920 --> 47:25.630
One moment you're lost in a carnival
of delight, childhood aromas,

47:25.800 --> 47:27.870
<i>the flashing neon of puberty,</i>

47:28.040 --> 47:31.077
all that sentimental candyfloss.

47:31.280 --> 47:35.558
The next, it takes you
somewhere you don't want to be.

47:35.720 --> 47:37.790
Somewhere dark and cold,

47:38.000 --> 47:42.278
filled with damp, ambiguous-shaped things
you'd rather forget.

47:42.760 --> 47:46.389
<i>Memories can be vile,
repulsive little brutes.</i>

47:46.800 --> 47:48.438
Like children, no?

47:48.600 --> 47:49.999
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GIGGLING MANIACALLY)</font></b>

47:50.160 --> 47:51.388
Barbara.

47:51.560 --> 47:52.788
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

47:53.960 --> 47:55.996
But can we live without them?

47:56.160 --> 47:58.549
Memories are what our reason is based on.

47:58.720 --> 48:01.632
If we deny them, we deny reason itself.

48:01.800 --> 48:04.598
Although, what's wrong with that, really?

48:04.760 --> 48:07.957
It's not like we're contractually
tied down to rationality.

48:08.560 --> 48:11.358
There is no sanity clause.

48:11.520 --> 48:12.919
So when you find yourself

48:13.080 --> 48:15.435
locked onto an unpleasant
train of thought,

48:15.600 --> 48:19.229
headed for places in your past
where the screaming is unavoidable...

48:19.400 --> 48:24.155
Remember this, there's always madness.

48:24.320 --> 48:26.629
You can just step outside,

48:26.840 --> 48:30.753
<i>close the door on all
those dreadful things that happened.</i>

48:30.920 --> 48:34.629
You can lock them away forever.

48:43.320 --> 48:45.040
<b><font color="#808080">THUG:</font></b> So, everything's
settled for tonight?

48:46.120 --> 48:47.553
We can count on you?

48:48.360 --> 48:50.430
Uh... Well, of course.

48:50.600 --> 48:52.397
It'd be crazy to back out now.

48:53.040 --> 48:55.918
I mean, the worst part,
lying to Jeannie, that's done.

48:56.600 --> 48:58.272
She thinks I have a club engagement.

48:58.480 --> 49:00.835
No reason she shouldn't
keep right on thinking that.

49:01.040 --> 49:04.396
Now, about tonight,
wear a suit and a bow tie.

49:04.560 --> 49:07.518
It's kind of the trademark
with this Red Hood business.

49:07.680 --> 49:10.114
It's what Jeannie
will expect me to wear to the night club.

49:10.280 --> 49:11.599
Ah! It's perfect.

49:14.480 --> 49:15.879
Excuse me, sir?

49:16.040 --> 49:18.508
Could we speak to you outside
for a moment?

49:20.240 --> 49:23.789
Me? But why?
I haven't, I mean, uh...

49:24.160 --> 49:25.718
It'll only take a moment, sir.

49:39.080 --> 49:40.433
<b><font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font></b>

50:03.560 --> 50:05.596
Something you want to tell us, friend?

50:07.040 --> 50:09.076
There was an accident this morning...

50:09.560 --> 50:11.312
Testing the baby bottle heater.

50:12.200 --> 50:16.113
An electrical short and my wife died.

50:18.400 --> 50:21.517
Gee, that's terrible. We're really sorry.

50:22.120 --> 50:24.918
The cops said it was
a million-to-one shot accident.

50:25.360 --> 50:28.432
Said I should probably have another drink
before I went to the hospital.

50:28.600 --> 50:29.749
And you should.

50:29.960 --> 50:33.509
Rough break, man,
probably want to be alone, right?

50:33.720 --> 50:34.789
That's cool.

50:35.000 --> 50:36.592
We'll see you back here tonight.

50:37.200 --> 50:38.269
Tonight?

50:38.920 --> 50:40.035
I can't.

50:40.320 --> 50:42.276
There's no reason anymore.

50:42.440 --> 50:44.874
Jeannie's dead.

50:45.040 --> 50:47.952
Oh, no, no, no, I'm sorry about your wife,

50:48.120 --> 50:50.918
but what's happening tonight,
it's no little thing.

50:51.800 --> 50:55.634
And we can't ensure that
anybody backing out remains healthy.

50:55.800 --> 50:58.872
- Uh, but...
- No buts and no exceptions.

50:59.040 --> 51:01.952
Look, tomorrow you bury
your old lady in luxury.

51:02.160 --> 51:04.071
Tonight, you're with us.

51:05.400 --> 51:07.072
Get the picture?

51:27.520 --> 51:29.238
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

51:29.800 --> 51:30.869
<b><font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font></b>

51:33.920 --> 51:35.512
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BREATHING HEAVILY)</font></b>

51:37.760 --> 51:38.954
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

51:39.200 --> 51:40.918
I'm going to count to 10.

51:41.240 --> 51:42.992
One, nine...

51:43.240 --> 51:45.356
I swear to God, man, he ain't been around.

51:45.640 --> 51:47.232
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font></b>
- Swear to me!

51:47.480 --> 51:49.357
You! I swear to you.

51:49.520 --> 51:52.796
When he escapes, it ain't long till he
comes around, recruiting, you know?

51:53.040 --> 51:55.110
But not this time. Nobody's seen him.

51:56.120 --> 51:57.394
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

52:02.760 --> 52:03.909
<b><font color="#808080">MAN:</font></b> Yeah?

52:05.160 --> 52:06.878
Step away from the door.

52:07.400 --> 52:08.594
Oh, shit.

52:09.280 --> 52:10.280
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMS)</font></b>

52:18.560 --> 52:20.391
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

52:24.000 --> 52:25.149
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font></b>

52:26.160 --> 52:27.309
You done?

52:30.160 --> 52:33.311
<i>- Yeah, I heard he got out again.</i>
- You heard?

52:33.960 --> 52:35.075
Read.

52:35.680 --> 52:38.478
Calm down, I have no idea where he is

52:38.640 --> 52:40.835
or what in the hell
he's got planned, trust me.

52:41.000 --> 52:42.479
I can't trust you.

52:42.680 --> 52:44.432
No, but believe me.

52:44.640 --> 52:47.438
If I knew anything, I'd tell you, honest.

52:47.640 --> 52:49.039
People in my, uh...

52:49.200 --> 52:50.519
Let's call it "line of work."

52:50.800 --> 52:51.869
Criminals.

52:52.040 --> 52:54.713
Yeah, we may be scared of you.

52:55.240 --> 52:56.798
We're terrified of him.

53:14.440 --> 53:16.635
Order in the court! Order in the court!

53:16.800 --> 53:18.279
I'll have ham on rye.

53:18.440 --> 53:19.919
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALL GROAN IN DISGUST)</font></b>

53:20.080 --> 53:23.072
It doesn't have to be good
to be a classic.

53:23.720 --> 53:27.235
So, Commissioner, I need your help.

53:27.400 --> 53:28.879
Is that why I'm here?

53:29.040 --> 53:30.871
That's why you're here right now,

53:31.040 --> 53:34.476
like right now, as in this moment.

53:34.720 --> 53:37.393
Do me a favor and live in it, okay?

53:37.560 --> 53:39.835
Anyway, me and my colleagues,
we couldn't come up with

53:40.000 --> 53:42.309
one sound mind and body between us.

53:42.480 --> 53:44.948
So, we're counting on yours.

53:45.240 --> 53:48.312
What should be done with someone
who has no regard for the law?

53:48.480 --> 53:50.789
- <b><font color="#808080">ALL:</font></b> Yeah!
- <b><font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font></b> He's right.

53:50.960 --> 53:53.554
Someone who treats people like meat!

53:54.000 --> 53:57.629
A man who has no problem
brutalizing his fellow man to get his way.

53:57.800 --> 53:59.995
- Now, now.
- What would you do to a man

54:00.160 --> 54:02.879
who breaks the laws
you are sworn to uphold?

54:03.040 --> 54:06.157
A monster who ignores
everything you stand for!

54:06.560 --> 54:08.949
Come on, is it that bad?

54:09.200 --> 54:12.158
Yes, it is, and if it were up to me...

54:12.400 --> 54:13.628
Right now, it is.

54:14.320 --> 54:15.912
I'd throw the book at him.

54:16.080 --> 54:17.320
<b><font color="#808080">ALL:</font></b> <b><font color="#D900D9">(CHANTING)</font></b>
Throw the book!

54:17.440 --> 54:20.671
Throw the book!
Throw the book! Throw the book!

54:24.480 --> 54:26.471
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHANTING CONTINUES)</font></b>

54:30.360 --> 54:34.035
What are you waiting for?
Throw it! Throw it!

54:34.480 --> 54:38.075
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(ALL CONTINUE CHANTING)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#808080">JOKER:</font></b> <i>Throw it! Throw it!</i>

54:38.240 --> 54:39.514
Throw the book!

54:42.880 --> 54:44.518
Right on target.

54:44.680 --> 54:46.033
Truth is, Commissioner,

54:46.200 --> 54:49.715
the man on trial here,
you consider your friend.

54:55.800 --> 54:57.950
<b><font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font></b>
Nope, which is funny.

54:58.120 --> 54:59.155
Funny?

54:59.320 --> 55:01.914
Yeah, he usually comes
around here, right away.

55:02.080 --> 55:03.513
Like before it's even on the news,

55:03.680 --> 55:05.830
he broke out of the nuthouse again,
he's had a roll.

55:06.040 --> 55:08.998
You'd think the most important
thing for him is to...

55:09.480 --> 55:10.674
What?

55:11.600 --> 55:13.397
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GIGGLING)</font></b>
- Have a good time.

55:13.760 --> 55:15.990
So, why do you think
he hasn't been to visit?

55:16.400 --> 55:17.400
I don't know.

55:17.560 --> 55:19.437
Maybe, he found himself another girl.

55:19.600 --> 55:21.477
Hey, somebody wants you.

55:26.320 --> 55:28.276
<b><font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERING)</font></b>

55:30.080 --> 55:32.548
<i>Uh-uh-uh. No fair hiding.</i>

55:33.320 --> 55:34.594
<b><font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERING)</font></b>

55:36.240 --> 55:39.038
<i>Ugh. Well, I'd see why.</i>

55:39.200 --> 55:41.555
<i>You don't look so good.</i>

55:41.840 --> 55:45.150
<i>Well, I don't blame you, not when that
bowl of cherries some call life,</i>

55:45.360 --> 55:48.158
<i>turned out to be the pits of hell.</i>
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b>

55:48.480 --> 55:52.439
<i>Perhaps, a song might
bring a smile to your face.</i>

55:57.280 --> 55:59.714
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SINGING)</font></b>
<i>When the world is full of care</i>

55:59.880 --> 56:02.474
<i>And every headline screams despair</i>

56:02.640 --> 56:08.078
<i>When all is rape,
starvation, war and life is vile</i>

56:08.920 --> 56:11.798
<i>Then there's a certain thing I do</i>

56:11.960 --> 56:14.793
<i>Which I shall pass along to you</i>

56:14.960 --> 56:20.318
<i>That's always guaranteed
to make me smile</i>

56:20.800 --> 56:22.597
<i>Yes!</i>

56:22.760 --> 56:26.230
<i>I go loony</i>

56:26.440 --> 56:29.273
<i>As a light bulb-battered bug</i>

56:29.440 --> 56:32.352
<i>Simply loony</i>

56:32.520 --> 56:35.114
<i>Sometimes foam and chew the rug</i>

56:35.280 --> 56:38.716
<i>Mister, life is swell in a padded cell</i>

56:38.880 --> 56:41.678
<i>It'll chase those blues away</i>

56:41.840 --> 56:44.513
<i>You can trade your gloom
for a rubber room</i>

56:44.680 --> 56:47.069
<i>And injections twice a day</i>

56:47.480 --> 56:50.392
<i>Just go loony like an acid casualty</i>

56:50.560 --> 56:53.916
<i>Or a Moonie or a preacher on TV</i>

56:54.680 --> 56:56.511
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font></b>

56:57.080 --> 57:02.108
<i>When the human race wears
an anxious face</i>

57:02.720 --> 57:05.757
<i>When the bomb hangs overhead</i>

57:05.920 --> 57:08.593
<i>When your kid turns blue</i>

57:08.760 --> 57:11.399
<i>It won't worry you</i>

57:11.560 --> 57:14.313
<i>You can smile and nod instead</i>

57:14.480 --> 57:17.358
<i>When you're loony</i>

57:17.520 --> 57:20.239
<i>Then you just don't give a fig</i>

57:20.400 --> 57:23.676
<i>Man's so puny</i>

57:23.840 --> 57:26.149
<i>And the universe so big</i>

57:26.320 --> 57:27.878
Barbara? No!

57:28.080 --> 57:29.672
<i>If you hurt inside, get certified</i>

57:29.880 --> 57:32.599
<i>And if life should treat you bad</i>

57:32.800 --> 57:34.199
Barbara! Barbara!

57:34.360 --> 57:37.955
<i>Don't get even, get mad</i>

57:38.120 --> 57:40.350
Barbara!

57:40.680 --> 57:41.874
Yes!

58:00.880 --> 58:03.110
Ah, here they are now.

58:04.720 --> 58:08.269
Holy Christ! That must be
the best ghost train in the business.

58:08.720 --> 58:10.756
I mean, when they went in,
the fellow in the middle

58:10.960 --> 58:13.235
didn't look a day over 17.

58:13.800 --> 58:17.554
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font></b> Well, that's what
a dose of reality will do to you.

58:17.840 --> 58:20.229
It's why I never touch the stuff.

58:20.520 --> 58:23.751
I find it waters down the hallucinations.

58:24.600 --> 58:27.034
So, Commissioner, how's things?

58:29.840 --> 58:32.912
Commissioner? Hello?
Anybody home?

58:36.040 --> 58:39.191
Oh. This wasn't supposed to
turn out boring.

58:39.760 --> 58:41.830
Oh, put him away in his cage.

58:42.000 --> 58:43.752
We're about to open for business.

58:44.200 --> 58:47.272
Let's hope our main
attraction gets livelier.

58:47.440 --> 58:50.432
Give him time to reflect upon life

58:50.600 --> 58:54.752
and all its random uncontrollability.

59:01.840 --> 59:04.070
<b><font color="#808080">THUG #1:</font></b> <i>Hey, quit your
daydreaming, friend.</i>

59:04.240 --> 59:05.355
<i>It's showtime.</i>

59:06.080 --> 59:07.991
I was just remembering.

59:09.120 --> 59:11.680
I used to walk along here
to work each morning.

59:11.840 --> 59:13.637
Ah, that's good, real good.

59:13.800 --> 59:15.472
That's just what we need you to do.

59:15.640 --> 59:17.640
<b><font color="#808080">THUG #2:</font></b> Just guide us through
this stinking factory

59:17.720 --> 59:19.870
so we can get to the joint next door.

59:20.040 --> 59:23.157
And stay far away from us
while we do the dirty work.

59:23.400 --> 59:27.109
It's like we're practically giving you
money by cutting you in on this.

59:27.280 --> 59:28.474
Right now?

59:28.640 --> 59:30.153
Will I be able to breathe?

59:30.320 --> 59:31.639
Not if you smoke.

59:32.280 --> 59:33.838
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b>
That's a good one.

59:34.000 --> 59:37.675
Maybe, I should be looking into your line
of work instead of you looking into mine.

59:38.200 --> 59:39.758
You got a funny shaped head.

59:40.120 --> 59:42.918
Maybe I should've been a clown
instead of a comedian.

59:43.240 --> 59:45.310
There. You can see, friend?

59:45.840 --> 59:48.115
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ECHOES)</font></b>
<i>Yeah, but everything's red,</i>

59:48.520 --> 59:51.239
stuffy too and it smells.

59:51.440 --> 59:52.839
Ooh, my voice sounds echo-y.

59:53.000 --> 59:55.594
<b><font color="#808080">THUG #2:</font></b> Then shut up
and get to work.

59:59.560 --> 01:00:02.870
<b><font color="#808080">RED HOOD:</font></b> Okay, we go through here
past the filter tanks

01:00:03.040 --> 01:00:06.077
and then Monarch Playing Cards
is just beyond the partition.

01:00:06.760 --> 01:00:09.035
<i>You know this place looks
even worse in red.</i>

01:00:10.040 --> 01:00:12.110
- It looks like...
- <b><font color="#808080">GUARD:</font></b> Hey, you! Freeze!

01:00:12.520 --> 01:00:13.680
Come on, come on, get 'em up!

01:00:18.760 --> 01:00:20.416
Murph, get some men over to the rear bays.

01:00:20.440 --> 01:00:22.396
We're being robbed by the Red Hood Mob.

01:00:24.800 --> 01:00:27.109
You asshole!
You said there was no security.

01:00:27.280 --> 01:00:29.296
<b><font color="#808080">RED HOOD:</font></b> They must have altered things
since I left.

01:00:29.320 --> 01:00:31.709
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(AIR HISSING)</font></b>
- It's so loud.

01:00:31.880 --> 01:00:34.917
For God's sake, run!
This is all screwed up, run!

01:00:40.400 --> 01:00:41.400
Man, which way?

01:00:41.560 --> 01:00:43.232
I can't see where I'm going.

01:00:43.400 --> 01:00:45.277
You useless son of a bitch.

01:00:45.440 --> 01:00:46.998
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GROANS)</font></b>

01:00:48.080 --> 01:00:49.559
I'm not the guy you want.

01:00:49.720 --> 01:00:51.995
It's him! He's our ringleader.

01:00:52.160 --> 01:00:53.593
He's the Red Hood.

01:00:56.240 --> 01:00:57.559
<b><font color="#808080">GUARD:</font></b> He's pulling a gun!

01:00:59.160 --> 01:01:00.160
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:01:01.080 --> 01:01:02.752
No, no, no, no, no!

01:01:04.480 --> 01:01:05.480
<b><font color="#808080">BATMAN:</font></b> Stop!

01:01:05.920 --> 01:01:07.399
No more shooting.

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:09.911
I'll take care of this my way.

01:01:11.040 --> 01:01:12.917
It's that human bat guy.

01:01:13.080 --> 01:01:15.435
<b><font color="#808080">RED HOOD:</font></b> Dear God,
what did I do to deserve this?

01:01:15.680 --> 01:01:17.113
<b><font color="#808080">BATMAN:</font></b> So, Red Hood,

01:01:19.200 --> 01:01:20.758
we meet again.

01:01:22.040 --> 01:01:25.430
Stay away from me,
don't come any closer, you monster!

01:01:25.680 --> 01:01:27.750
Uh, uh... <b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font></b>

01:01:44.640 --> 01:01:45.993
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

01:01:46.640 --> 01:01:47.914
It burns!

01:01:51.120 --> 01:01:53.953
I'm itching all over. What's...

01:01:57.640 --> 01:01:59.631
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font></b>

01:02:01.960 --> 01:02:03.678
<b><font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font></b>

01:02:10.800 --> 01:02:12.631
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)</font></b>

01:02:29.720 --> 01:02:32.234
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

01:02:39.240 --> 01:02:41.356
<b><font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font></b>

01:02:53.520 --> 01:02:55.715
<b><font color="#808080">JOKER:</font></b> <b><font color="#D900D9">(ON PA)</font></b>
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:02:55.880 --> 01:02:58.030
<i>although there doesn't
seem to be either here.</i>

01:02:58.200 --> 01:03:00.668
<i>How about children of all ages?</i>

01:03:01.200 --> 01:03:05.113
<i>You must have received your free ticket.
Oh, I'm so glad.</i>

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:08.877
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CAROUSEL MUSIC PLAYING)</font></b>

01:03:10.520 --> 01:03:12.317
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:03:24.200 --> 01:03:25.997
<b><font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC SLOWS AND STOPS)</font></b>

01:03:31.400 --> 01:03:32.400
<b><font color="#D900D9">(FLOOR CREAKING)</font></b>

01:03:33.200 --> 01:03:35.111
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:03:42.320 --> 01:03:43.469
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:03:52.000 --> 01:03:53.399
<b><font color="#D900D9">(COUGHING)</font></b>

01:03:59.800 --> 01:04:01.677
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:04:03.520 --> 01:04:04.520
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:04:12.960 --> 01:04:14.109
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROWLS)</font></b>

01:04:14.400 --> 01:04:16.436
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:04:19.320 --> 01:04:21.550
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING AND BARKING)</font></b>

01:04:30.560 --> 01:04:33.632
Ladies and gentlemen,
children of all ages,

01:04:33.800 --> 01:04:36.872
I give you the average man.

01:04:38.960 --> 01:04:40.712
Impressive, eh?

01:04:40.880 --> 01:04:42.791
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)</font></b>

01:04:44.640 --> 01:04:47.438
Ooh! <b><font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES LAUGHING)</font></b>

01:04:47.720 --> 01:04:49.119
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:04:52.240 --> 01:04:53.798
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font></b>

01:05:02.640 --> 01:05:03.709
Jim.

01:05:03.920 --> 01:05:05.797
Jim, are you still...

01:05:06.320 --> 01:05:08.834
Oh, God. Oh, God.

01:05:10.840 --> 01:05:13.115
It's okay, let it come.

01:05:14.400 --> 01:05:17.915
He showed me pictures of my daughter.
Have you seen her?

01:05:18.840 --> 01:05:20.239
Yes, she's alive.

01:05:20.400 --> 01:05:21.515
And?

01:05:21.680 --> 01:05:23.432
The police are right behind me.

01:05:23.600 --> 01:05:24.749
I'll stay with you, until...

01:05:24.920 --> 01:05:27.275
No, I'll survive.

01:05:27.960 --> 01:05:31.555
Go after him. I want him brought in.

01:05:31.720 --> 01:05:33.711
And I want it done by the book.

01:05:37.480 --> 01:05:39.152
By the book!

01:05:39.320 --> 01:05:40.912
You have to!

01:05:41.400 --> 01:05:44.517
We have to show him our way works.

01:05:54.880 --> 01:05:56.871
<b><font color="#808080">JOKER:</font></b> <i>Let me ask you something.</i>

01:05:57.040 --> 01:06:01.477
<i>What does it matter if you send me back to
the asylum if it doesn't matter to me?</i>

01:06:03.720 --> 01:06:05.278
I've proved my point.

01:06:05.480 --> 01:06:07.198
Gordon's been driven mad.

01:06:07.400 --> 01:06:12.110
<i>I've demonstrated there's no difference
between me and everyone else.</i>

01:06:13.400 --> 01:06:17.029
<i>All it takes is one bad day.</i>

01:06:17.240 --> 01:06:19.549
<i>That's how far the world
is from where I am,</i>

01:06:19.720 --> 01:06:21.790
just one bad day.

01:06:22.880 --> 01:06:24.472
<i>You had a bad day once, am I right?</i>

01:06:24.640 --> 01:06:26.915
<i>Oh, I know I am.</i>

01:06:27.080 --> 01:06:28.149
<i>I can tell.</i>

01:06:28.320 --> 01:06:31.153
<i>You had a bad day
and everything changed.</i>

01:06:31.400 --> 01:06:34.631
<i>Dressing up like a flying rat
doesn't hide it, it screams it.</i>

01:06:34.840 --> 01:06:37.354
<i>You had a bad day
and it drove you as crazy</i>

01:06:37.520 --> 01:06:40.671
<i>as everybody else,
only you won't admit it.</i>

01:06:40.840 --> 01:06:42.056
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>
<i>- You have to keep pretending</i>

01:06:42.080 --> 01:06:43.195
<i>that life makes sense,</i>

01:06:43.360 --> 01:06:45.794
<i>that there's some point
to all this struggling.</i>

01:06:45.960 --> 01:06:48.076
<i>You make me want to puke.</i>

01:06:50.240 --> 01:06:51.593
<b><font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font></b>

01:06:54.280 --> 01:06:56.430
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(CATS SCREECHING)</font></b>
- Shh.

01:06:57.920 --> 01:07:00.309
<i>I mean, what is it with you?</i>

01:07:00.480 --> 01:07:03.119
<i>What made you what you are?</i>

01:07:03.760 --> 01:07:06.228
<i>Girlfriend killed by the mob, maybe?</i>

01:07:06.400 --> 01:07:08.311
<i>Brother carved up by some mugger?</i>

01:07:08.480 --> 01:07:10.232
<i>Something like that, I know.</i>

01:07:10.400 --> 01:07:13.631
<i>Because something like that
happened to me.</i>

01:07:19.560 --> 01:07:23.473
<i>Sometimes, I remember it one way,
sometimes another.</i>

01:07:24.040 --> 01:07:25.871
<i>If I'm going to have a past,</i>

01:07:26.200 --> 01:07:28.873
<i>I prefer it to be multiple choice.</i>

01:07:30.600 --> 01:07:32.033
<i>My point is...</i>

01:07:33.800 --> 01:07:36.439
I went crazy.

01:07:37.760 --> 01:07:40.228
And I'm smart enough to admit it.

01:07:40.800 --> 01:07:42.518
Why can't you?

01:07:43.360 --> 01:07:44.360
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:07:44.520 --> 01:07:48.513
By clinging to reality, you're denying
the reality of the situation.

01:07:48.760 --> 01:07:50.318
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font></b>

01:07:51.720 --> 01:07:52.720
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:07:52.920 --> 01:07:55.388
I mean, do you ever think
about how many times

01:07:55.560 --> 01:07:59.838
we've come close to World War III over
a flock of geese on a computer screen?

01:08:00.720 --> 01:08:02.472
Silly goose, it's all a joke,

01:08:02.680 --> 01:08:07.674
everything anybody's ever valued
or struggled for, it's monstrous.

01:08:07.840 --> 01:08:10.673
Why can't you see the funny side?

01:08:11.760 --> 01:08:14.957
Why aren't you laughing?

01:08:15.200 --> 01:08:16.599
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:08:19.720 --> 01:08:21.517
Because I've heard it before,

01:08:21.920 --> 01:08:24.434
and it wasn't funny the first time.

01:08:25.200 --> 01:08:27.350
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)</font></b>

01:08:27.760 --> 01:08:29.671
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:08:32.040 --> 01:08:35.032
I spoke with Commissioner Gordon
before I came in here.

01:08:35.279 --> 01:08:37.635
He told me he wanted
this done by the book.

01:08:38.080 --> 01:08:39.399
You know what that means?

01:08:39.560 --> 01:08:43.234
It means that despite all your sick,
cruel, vicious little games,

01:08:43.399 --> 01:08:45.515
he's as sane as he ever was.

01:08:45.720 --> 01:08:48.553
So, ordinary people don't crack.

01:08:50.080 --> 01:08:52.799
Maybe it's just you.

01:08:56.040 --> 01:08:57.439
- No!
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:08:58.399 --> 01:09:00.310
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font></b>

01:09:06.240 --> 01:09:07.240
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:09:10.120 --> 01:09:11.519
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:09:21.080 --> 01:09:22.832
God damn it.

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:24.274
Well, what are you waiting for?

01:09:24.439 --> 01:09:27.716
Kick the hell out of me
and get your standing ovation.

01:09:30.439 --> 01:09:31.714
Come on!

01:09:32.319 --> 01:09:34.356
No, not this time.

01:09:37.160 --> 01:09:38.559
I don't want to hurt you.

01:09:38.920 --> 01:09:41.673
I don't want either of us
to end up killing the other.

01:09:41.840 --> 01:09:43.591
But we're running out of alternatives.

01:09:44.359 --> 01:09:46.270
Perhaps it all hinges on tonight.

01:09:47.319 --> 01:09:51.313
I don't know what it was
that bent your life out of shape,

01:09:51.479 --> 01:09:54.040
but maybe I've been there, too.

01:09:54.560 --> 01:09:56.152
Maybe we could work together.

01:09:56.400 --> 01:09:58.072
I could rehabilitate you.

01:09:58.720 --> 01:10:00.790
You don't need to be alone.

01:10:00.960 --> 01:10:02.951
We don't have to kill each other.

01:10:05.560 --> 01:10:07.152
Let me help you.

01:10:13.360 --> 01:10:15.794
I'm sorry, but no.

01:10:17.760 --> 01:10:21.070
No, it's far too late for that.

01:10:27.600 --> 01:10:29.989
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font></b>

01:10:30.440 --> 01:10:32.829
You know, it's funny.

01:10:33.560 --> 01:10:35.278
This reminds me of a joke.

01:10:35.840 --> 01:10:39.150
See, there were two guys
locked in a lunatic asylum

01:10:39.320 --> 01:10:42.471
and one night, one night they decided
they didn't like that anymore.

01:10:42.640 --> 01:10:44.153
They decided to escape.

01:10:44.320 --> 01:10:45.856
So, they made it up to the roof and there,

01:10:45.880 --> 01:10:48.235
just across this narrow gap,
they see rooftops,

01:10:48.400 --> 01:10:51.517
stretching across town,
stretching to freedom.

01:10:51.720 --> 01:10:54.314
Now, the first guy,
he jumps right across, no problem.

01:10:54.520 --> 01:10:58.115
But his friend, <b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b> no way,
he's afraid of falling.

01:10:58.280 --> 01:11:00.236
So, the first guy, he has an idea.

01:11:00.440 --> 01:11:03.318
He says,
"Hey, I got this flashlight with me.

01:11:03.480 --> 01:11:05.516
"I'll shine it across the gap
between the buildings

01:11:05.680 --> 01:11:08.399
"and you can walk across
the beam and join me."

01:11:08.560 --> 01:11:11.120
But the second guy says,
"What do you think I am, crazy?

01:11:11.280 --> 01:11:14.477
"You'll just turn it off
when I'm halfway across."

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:19.072
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font></b> Excuse me.

01:11:23.840 --> 01:11:25.114
Hmm.

01:11:25.280 --> 01:11:26.280
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BATMAN CHUCKLES)</font></b>

01:11:30.720 --> 01:11:32.836
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font></b>

01:11:37.880 --> 01:11:40.110
<b><font color="#D900D9">(JOKER STOPS LAUGHING)</font></b>

01:12:26.360 --> 01:12:28.635
<b><font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font></b>

01:12:41.880 --> 01:12:44.713
Yeah, Dad, I just got back
from the lacrosse game.

01:12:46.320 --> 01:12:48.675
Going to practice
some Wallball this weekend.

01:12:52.120 --> 01:12:53.519
Getting pretty good.

01:12:56.800 --> 01:12:59.155
Maybe another night, Dad,
I got plans tonight.

01:12:59.840 --> 01:13:02.115
I can't help it
if your daughter's so popular.

01:13:02.760 --> 01:13:04.113
I'll talk to you, later.

01:13:04.720 --> 01:13:05.914
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PHONE BEEPS)</font></b>

01:13:09.480 --> 01:13:11.311
<b><font color="#D900D9">(POWERING UP)</font></b>

01:13:24.280 --> 01:13:26.919
Right then, back to work.
